        "topicTag": "functions",
        "text": "Which of the following is an arrow function?",
        "options": [
          {
            "id": "q2-1-a",
            "text": "function add(a, b) { return a + b; }",
            "isCorrect": false
          },
          {
            "id": "q2-1-b",
            "text": "const add = (a, b) => a + b;",
            "isCorrect": true
          },
          {
            "id": "q2-1-c",
            "text": "add = function(a, b) { return a + b; }",
            "isCorrect": false
          },
          {
            "id": "q2-1-d",
            "text": "def add(a, b): return a + b",
            "isCorrect": false
          }
        ],
        "explanation": "Arrow functions use the => syntax, introduced in ES6."
      },
      {
        "id": "q2-2",
        "testId": "test-2",
        "type": "true_false",
        "topicTag": "scope",
        "text": "Arrow functions have their own 'this' binding.",
        "options": [
          {
            "id": "q2-2-a",
            "text": "True",
            "isCorrect": false
          },
          {
            "id": "q2-2-b",
            "text": "False",
            "isCorrect": true
          }
        ],
        "explanation": "Arrow functions do NOT have their own 'this'. They inherit 'this' from the enclosing lexical context."
      },
